This paper is primarily focused on cryptographic protocols and their security, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). It also discusses the concept of secure compilation, which is related to programming languages and compilers, and could be classified under cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also involves mathematical proofs and formal methods, which could be categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
